Let’s have a closer look on the @artisansdegeneve personalization realized for the double world champion of F1 - Mika Häkkinen. Artisans de Genève turned Mikas Daytona into a skeleton version featuring a manual winding movement.

The exclusive color combination of orange and blue reminds the race tracks the F1 legend triumphed on. Every element is a tribute to his legendary career, the dial features an exclusive design inspired from a steering wheel, while the skeletonization of the movement recalls the mechanics of a F1 engine. 

Artisans de Genève is an independent company specialized in the personalization of timepieces. Artisans de Genève is not affiliated with ROLEX SA nor authorized by them to intervene on their products for any reason whatsoever. This personalization was ordered for his private use by a customer who owns a Rolex® timepiece.

Behind the scene of the exclusive partnership between @Jacobandco and Bugatti. 
The amazing assembly of the jaw dropping Chiron Tourbillon 🔬✍🏻

The case is inspired by the flowing lines of the Chiron and the movement, or “engine block,” intended to duplicate the Bugatti engine, is placed under a massive sapphire crystal, on display for all to see. With the push of right-hand crown of the timepiece the engine comes to life, just like a true internal combustion engine. 
The movement is set with a total of 578 exquisite components. 
Right now Jacob’s workshop is doing something no one has ever even attempted before: to seamlessly combine engines and watches💯

node.text: At the Us Open 2021 with @wristaficionado and its amazing Richard Mille RM35 Baby Nadal. The tonneau-shaped case is signature Richard Mille, and is made of an ultra-light magnesium-aluminum alloy. This alloy is composed of 90% magnesium and 8.9% aluminum and helps keep this beauty under 50 grams. Now available at @wristaficionado boutique 🇺🇸
